This paper examines a social media activism campaign and its impact on improving gender diversity within engineering. The study analyzes over 50,000 tweets and categorizes triggers that increased activity at crucial moments. The paper's focus on social media, activism, and diversity suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computers and Society (cs.CY), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
